# Beads CLI Reference (bd)

The `bd` binary is the Beads CLI. All beads operations in Monkeyland go through the Tauri `beads_run` command which shells out to `bd`.

## CRITICAL: Valid commands

There is **NO** `bd archive` command. Calling it silently fails. Use these instead:

| Action | Command | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|
| Close issue(s) | `bd close <id> [--reason "..."]` | Marks as closed, preserves history |
| Delete issue(s) | `bd delete <id> --force` | Destructive, removes from DB |
| Reopen issue(s) | `bd reopen <id>` | Sets status back to open |

## Commands used by Monkeyland

### Listing tasks
```
bd list --json --all          # All tasks including closed (for inspection/dedup)
bd list --json                # Only open/in-progress tasks
bd ready --json               # Ready tasks (open, no blockers)
bd children <parent-id> --json
```

`--all` is critical for deduplication â€” without it, closed tasks are hidden and the hard-block on duplicate epics won't see completed ones.

### Creating tasks
```
bd create <title> --silent --type <type> --priority <n> [--parent <id>] [--description "..."] [--deps "id1,id2"] [--labels "l1,l2"] [--acceptance "..."] [--estimate <minutes>] [--defer "+100y"]
```
- `--silent` outputs only the new issue ID (for scripting)
- Types: `epic`, `task`, `feature`, `bug`, `chore`, `decision`
- `--defer "+100y"` creates hidden draft tasks (used by PM agents)

### Closing / cleanup
```
bd close <id> [--reason "..."]    # Close one issue
bd close id1 id2 id3             # Close multiple
bd close --force                  # Force-close pinned issues
```

### Updating tasks
```
bd update <id> --status <status> [--title "..."] [--description "..."] [--assignee "..."]
```
- Statuses: `open`, `in_progress`, `blocked`, `deferred`, `closed`

### Other useful commands
```
bd show <id> --json           # Full issue details
bd delete <id> --force        # Permanent deletion
bd delete <id> --cascade --force  # Delete with all dependents
bd find-duplicates            # AI-powered duplicate detection
bd status                     # Database overview
bd types                      # Valid issue types
```

## Tauri commands (invoke from frontend)

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `beads_dolt_start` | Start Dolt SQL server for the project. **Must run before any bd command.** Params: `{ projectPath, agentId }` |
| `beads_init` | Initialize beads in a project. Returns "Beads already initialized." if exists. Params: `{ projectPath, agentId }` |
| `beads_run` | Run any bd subcommand. Params: `{ projectPath, args: string[], agentId }` |
| `get_beads_project_path` | Read stored project path from MetaDb (persists across restarts) |
| `set_beads_project_path` | Store project path in MetaDb. Params: `{ projectPath, agentId }` |

## Common pitfalls

1. **Always start Dolt first** â€” `beads_dolt_start` must succeed before any `beads_run` call
2. **Use `--all` for dedup queries** â€” `bd list --json` hides closed tasks; use `--all` to see everything
3. **`bd archive` does NOT exist** â€” use `bd close` or `bd delete`
4. **`bd list` has a default limit of 50** â€” use `--limit 0` for unlimited, or `--all` which also removes the limit
5. **`--silent` on create** â€” returns only the ID string, critical for scripting
6. **MetaDb persists across restarts** â€” `get_beads_project_path` returns the last project path even after app restart
